Knight and Graehl (1998) used a bilingual English-katakana dictionary, a katakana-to-English phoneme mapping, and the CMU Speech Pronunciation Dictionary to create a series of weighted finite-state transducers between English words and katakana that produce and rank transliteration candidates.
J98-4003
Transliteration of names between alphabetic and syllabic scripts has also been studied for languages such as Japanese/English (Fujii & Ishikawa, 2001), English/Korean (Jeong et aal., 1999), and English/Arabic (Al-Onaizan and Knight, 2002).
W02-0505
